Chelsea has reached an agreement with RB Leipzig to sign striker Timo Werner, who was set to join the English side in July, the Premier League club announced on Thursday. “I’m delighted to be signing for Chelsea, it is a very proud moment for me to be joining this great club. “I of course want to thank RB Leipzig, the club and the fans, for four fantastic years. You will forever be in my heart. “I look forward to next season with my new teammates, my new manager and of course the Chelsea fans. Together we have a very successful future ahead of us,” Werner said in a statement.(Reuters/NAN) 